# Vue 3 / Frontend Standards

## Component Structure

Always in this order, include only what is needed:
```vue
<script setup lang="ts">
<template>
<style scoped>
```

- `<script setup lang="ts">` — required on every component. No Options API.
- Single responsibility: components handle **rendering only**. Logic and state go into composables.
- Composables handle **logic and state only**. No rendering or DOM concerns inside them.
- Utilities are **pure, stateless functions**. No Vue reactivity inside utility files.

## Props, Emits, Model

```ts
// Props — always typed, destructure for defaults (not withDefaults)
const { label = 'Default', count = 0 } = defineProps<{
  label?: string
  count?: number
}>()

// Emits — typed tuple format
const emit = defineEmits<{
  submit: [value: string]
  cancel: []
}>()

// v-model — use defineModel() (Vue 3.4+), not modelValue prop manually
const model = defineModel<string>()
```

- camelCase in `<script setup>`, kebab-case in templates
- `const props =` only when props are used inside `<script setup>` block

## Template Refs and Watchers

```ts
// Template refs — useTemplateRef() (Vue 3.5+), not $refs
const inputRef = useTemplateRef('inputRef')

// Watching props — always use a getter function
watch(() => props.count, (newVal) => { ... })
// ❌ watch(props.count, ...) — loses reactivity
```

## State Management (Pinia)

Use setup stores (`defineStore('name', () => {...})`):

```ts
export const useFeatureStore = defineStore('feature', () => {
  const items = ref<Item[]>([])
  const total = computed(() => items.value.length)

  async function loadItems() { ... }

  return { items, total, loadItems }
  // Return ALL state so Pinia devtools can track it
})
```

- **Pinia**: shared state that spans routes or unrelated component trees
- **`ref` / `computed`**: local component state
- **Server state** (API responses not needing local edits): fetch directly, don't copy into Pinia
- `storeToRefs()` when destructuring store state or getters — direct destructure breaks reactivity:

```ts
const store = useFeatureStore()
const { items, total } = storeToRefs(store) // ✅
const { loadItems } = store                  // actions destructure directly
```

## Composables

- Name: `useCamelCase.ts`, starts with `use`
- Extract when logic is used in 2+ components
- Prefer `MaybeRefOrGetter` + `toValue()` when accepting reactive arguments
- Prefer object arguments over multiple positional args

## Financial Values

- All monetary values arrive from API as **integers (kopecks)**
- Display: always use the shared `useFormatCurrency` composable — never inline the conversion
- Profit / positive delta → `text-green-*` token; Loss / negative → `text-red-*` token
- Never hardcoded hex for financial indicators

## Layout & Responsiveness

- **Desktop-first**: design for `1280px+`, adapt down with `md:` and default classes
- Breakpoints: `1280px` / `1024px` / `768px`
- Semantic HTML: `<main>`, `<section>`, `<article>`, `<label>`
- ARIA labels on all interactive elements without visible text

## Naming Conventions

| Type | Convention | Location |
|------|-----------|----------|
| Components | `PascalCase.vue` | `features/[name]/components/` or `components/ui/` |
| Composables | `useCamelCase.ts` | `composables/` or colocated |
| Stores | `useCamelCaseStore.ts` | `features/[name]/store/` or `stores/` |
| Types | `PascalCase` | `src/types/` or `feature/types.ts` |

## Pinia Anti-Patterns

- Do not destructure store state without `storeToRefs()`
- Do not put server-only objects, DOM nodes, or timers in store state
- Do not use Pinia as a dumping ground for every reactive value
- Do not create circular reads between stores in setup functions
